Residents of Meru last weekend were treated to a new range of sugarless beverages at the Meru Polytechnic grounds. The beverage range includes Coca-Cola, Sprite and Stoney. They were launched by Coca-Cola Central, East and West Africa Ltd and its bottling partner Coca-Cola Beverages Africa in Kenya to give consumers alternatives. Attendees were entertained by Khaligraph Jones, Nadia Mukami and Mugithi maestro Samido, with MC Jesse and Hype Da Goodaman hyping the crowd. Also in attendance were Coca Cola Beverages Africa in Kenya MD Xavier Selga, Almasi Beverages Limited CEO Joyce Macharia, ECAF head of marketing Nelly Wainaina and Coca -Cola customer and commercial director Oliver Soto.